lass, this strategy gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one prompt and asks it to cover the missing accesses in a single broad pass.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:535:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:548:    \"description\": \"Pi graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:553:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:567:    \"description\": \"Codex graphify-assisted bulk dynamic-access strategy. It first builds graphify context from downloaded source artifacts, then gives the agent the full dynamic-access report in one broad pass. Unlike the regular dynamic-access strategy, it does not run the class-by-class refinement loop.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:572:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:592:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:593:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:614:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:615:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:636:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:637:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:658:      \"optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:659:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:697:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:715:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:728:    \"description\": \"Library-update strategy: skips primary workflow, directly runs dynamic-access coverage improvement on existing tests.\",\n./forge/strategies/predefined_strategies.json:733:      \"dynamic-access-iteration\": \"prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md\"\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:3:description: Review pull requests with the `fixes-javac-fail` label in graalvm-reachability-metadata. Use when asked to review or triage a PR that fixes Java compilation failures for an existing library version update. Focus on validating the compile fix, keeping the diff scoped, and ensuring dynamic-access coverage does not drop between the previously tested version and the new version.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Native-image execution should remain enabled by default when the repaired test reaches the native lane. Do not accept changes that skip or short-circuit native-image behavior. When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally relies on open-ended dynamic class loading that native image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:20:- Treat dynamic-access coverage preservation as the main quality gate. The new version should not report lower dynamic-access coverage than the previously tested version unless the PR gives a concrete, credible reason.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:21:- For numeric gates, compare the reported evidence as-is. Do not inspect generation filters, agent configuration, or metadata contents to second-guess why dynamic-access or metadata-count numbers are what they are.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:50:   - Compatibility branches are acceptable when they keep older and newer tested versions covered by the same test.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:54:4. Check dynamic-access coverage across versions.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:56:   - Compare `dynamicAccess.coverageRatio`, `coveredCalls`, `totalCalls`, and the `dynamicAccess.breakdown` entries for reflection, resources, proxies, serialization, JNI, or any other present report type.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:57:   - Do not use `user-code-filter.json`, agent configuration, or metadata file contents to argue that the reported dynamic-access values are not comparable. Use the stats values as reported unless the stats are missing or stale.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:58:   - A lower `coverageRatio` or lower `coveredCalls` for the new version is blocking unless the total dynamic-access surface changed and the PR explains why the reduction is expected.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:59:   - If `totalCalls` increases while `coveredCalls` stays flat or the ratio drops, ask for additional test coverage or metadata unless the uncovered calls are clearly outside the library behavior under test.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - When the new total is below 25% of the original and the tests and dynamic-access stats still claim comparable coverage, ask for restored metadata or a concrete explanation of the API/package change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:107:- For coverage drops: say that dynamic-access coverage must not regress between tested versions, cite the old and new values, and ask for either restored coverage or a concrete explanation.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:154:        // Expected: Native Image cannot load generated classes discovered after build.\n./forge/git_scripts/make_pr_improve_coverage.py:73:This PR improves dynamic-access coverage for {coordinates} by generating additional tests.\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:656:    \"\"\"Format a single dynamic-access stats entry.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:657:    return \"{covered}/{total} covered calls ({ratio:.2f}%)\".format(\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:658:        covered=stats[\"coveredCalls\"],\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:665:    \"\"\"Return True when stats has the expected dynamic-access entry shape.\"\"\"\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:667:        key in stats for key in (\"coveredCalls\", \"totalCalls\", \"coverageRatio\")\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:675:    return \"{covered}/{total} ({ratio:.2f}%)\".format(\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:676:        covered=entry[\"covered\"],\n./forge/git_scripts/common_git.py:683:    \"\"\"Format the dynamic-access stats into a markdown section.\"\"\"\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** â€” generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and â€” when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) â€” opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:46:- A `stats/<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/stats.json` mirror of per-version metrics (dynamic-access call sites, coverage, lines of code, dependency information).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:55:- Coverage collection (JaCoCo) and dynamic-access reporting per coordinate.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:74:- `latest/badges.json` â€” badges shown in the README (libraries supported, tested versions, dynamic-access coverage, tested LOC).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:84:1. **Add new library support** â€” generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:87:4. **Improve coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered dynamic-access call sites.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:2:When the repository doesnâ€™t have reachability metadata for a library you are using, the easiest way to generate it is to execute the test suite of the library with the Native Image Agent enabled. The agent is installed together with native-image and can be used to identify elements used during application execution that cannot be discovered by static analysis.\n./docs/DEVELOPING.md:329:  Output: `metadata/<group>/<artifact>/<version>/test/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json`\n./docs/REVIEWING.md:57:All metadata files **must** be covered by the tests. Every metadata file should:\n./forge/prompt_templates/after-failed-iteration/basic_after_fail.md:2:Pick a different uncovered `{library}` feature and write tests for it.\n./forge/prompt_templates/initial/basic_initial.md:18:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:4:Improve test coverage for the active dynamic-access class in `{library}`.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:13:Progress since the previous dynamic-access report:\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:16:Remaining uncovered dynamic-access call sites for this class:\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:17:{uncovered_dynamic_access_calls}\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:20:- Add or refine tests so execution reaches the remaining uncovered call sites for the active class.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:23:- Maintain a one-to-one mapping between dynamic-access report classes and generated test class files.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:35:- When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally requires open-ended dynamic class loading that Native Image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, catch `Error`, verify it with `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`, and re-throw if it does not match. This proves Native Image fails for the right reason instead of skipping the test.\n./forge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/codex_after_success.md:4:- Read the current test file to determine which `{library}` features are already covered.\n./forge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/codex_after_success.md:5:- Identify additional uncovered features of `{library}` and add tests for it.\n./forge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/basic_after_success.md:3:- Identify a new, functional feature of the library `{library}` that is not yet covered by the existing tests, and write tests for it.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:4:Generate test for `{library}` following provided dynamic access report, by covering as many uncovered call sites as possible across