urces, serialization) are not yet covered by the generated tests. Instead of generating tests blindly, the workflow iterates class-by-class, sending the agent targeted prompts with the exact uncovered call sites for each class. After each attempt, the report is regenerated and coverage deltas are computed to decide whether to retry the same class or move on.\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:440:Composite strategies (run a primary workflow, then refine dynamic-access coverage):\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:447:#### Running a dynamic-access strategy\n./forge/DEVELOPING.md:469:For the detailed function-level notes and sequence diagram, see `docs/dynamic-access-strategy.md`.\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:38:    Strategies are discovered via a class-level registry. Use the\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/workflow_strategy.py:126:        (e.g. active_class_name, uncovered call sites).\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:12:    \"\"\"Composite strategy that runs a primary workflow then improves dynamic-access coverage.\"\"\"\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:35:            self._print_message(\"no primary workflow configured, skipping to dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:46:                self._print_message(\"skipping dynamic-access coverage phase because primary workflow did not succeed\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:52:        self._print_message(\"starting dynamic-access coverage phase\")\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:61:            \"dynamic-access coverage phase completed with phase_ok={phase_ok}, iterations_added={iterations}\".format(\n./forge/ai_workflows/workflow_strategies/increase_dynamic_access_coverage_strategy.py:68:            se